            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-05-30 16:09:18" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a meaningful mark, whether engraved, imprinted, or branded</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>mark</Gloss>
                <Gloss>brand</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>A strictly literal translation of ‘the mark of the beast’ might imply ‘a picture of the beast’ or ‘a mark made by the beast.’ A more satisfactory indication of the relationship between ‘mark’ and ‘beast’ would be ‘a mark showing one’s relationship to the beast’ or ‘a mark of loyalty to the beast’ or ‘a mark of the party of the beast.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
